HEADWORD: Wood hyacinth
<hw>Wood hyacinth</hw>. <def>A European squill (<spn>Scilla
nonscripta</spn>) having a scape bearing a raceme of drooping blue,
purple, white, or sometimes pink, bell-shaped flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

